  "code_change": {
    "description": "Add diagnostic --batch-sample-argmax-mode=serial_per_row / HIPENGINE_QWEN35_BATCH_SAMPLE_ARGMAX_MODE=serial_per_row. It keeps batched LM-head projection/norm but uses serial per-row argmax over the batched logits and records a sampler blocker so retained sampler claims remain blocked.",
    "files": [
      "hipengine/runtime/qwen35_paro_runner.py",
      "scripts/qwen35_batch_retained_bench.py",
      "tests/test_qwen35_resident_batch_layout.py"
    ]
  },
  "conclusion": "The c2 batched LM-head projection/norm path stayed generated-token-equality green under the same known-red c9 grouped stress when only the argmax half was forced to serial_per_row: all three c2 runs were [137,137]. This strongly narrows the explicit c2 batched-sampler post-c9 flake toward the batch_argmax_f32 path rather than the batched LM-head projection/norm logits. The serial_per_row argmax mode records a sampler blocker and is diagnostic only, not retained-ready. No throughput claim is made.",
